result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher David Winchell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Christopher David Winchell is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Christopher David Winchell was found guilty of Theft-Movable Property >$2500-$5000 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Christopher David Winchell was found guilty of Criminal Trespass to Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Defendant shall pay restitution in the amount of $2,500.00 to Timothy and Vicki Krenz, joint and several with Kole Figi and Kassandra Paulson.
Defendant is allowed work release privileges.

Defendant shall not have any direct or indirect contact with Timothy Krenz, Vicki Krenz, Thomas Krenz, Kole Figi, and Kassandra Paulson nor shall he go on the premises occupied by any of those parties.
Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcoholic beverages or nonprescription controlled substances, or any prescription medicine for which the defendant does not have a current prescription.
Defendant shall not enter into any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale of alcoholic beverages.
Defendant shall not possess any drug paraphernalia.

Defendant shall consent to a reasonable request of a law enforcement officer, based on probable cause, to submit to a breath, blood, saliva, or urine test for purposes of determining the quantity of alcohol or drugs in defendant's breath, blood, saliva, or urine.
Defendant shall submit a DNA sample.  
Defendant shall participate in any and all counseling deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and follow through with all recommendations thereof.

timeConds.notes:
Defendant shall serve 9 months in the Lafayette County Jail.  This sentence is consecutive to sentence imposed in Count 3.
Consecutive to: Consecutive to sentence in Count 3
